HEADWORD: Hackmatack
<hw>Hack"ma*tack`</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧k"m⟦adot⟧*t⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of American Indian origin.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The American larch (<spn>Larix Americana</spn>), a coniferous tree
with slender deciduous leaves; also, its heavy, close-grained timber.
Called also <altname>tamarack</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hackney</ent>⟦br⟧
